The glider landed hard on touchdown.  The student pilot encountered what witnesses 
described as a "really large" dust devil during the landing flare.  Thereafter, the glider's nose 
pitched downward, and the glider impacted the ground hard.  The student's traffic pattern 
approach to runway 24C had been normal.  The prevailing wind was from 240 degrees, 
between 5 and 10 knots.
